  "body": "### Description\nIt looks like our `/node/syncing` endpoint may report out-of-date syncing information for the `current_slot`. While we're syncing, [we skip onTick processing](https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/blob/a99f47058d37d21f57567b632a9cffe9c03e3ddc/services/beaconchain/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/artemis/services/beaconchain/BeaconChainController.java#L380-L382) which includes [updating our canonical head](https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/blob/a99f47058d37d21f57567b632a9cffe9c03e3ddc/ethereum/statetransition/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/artemis/statetransition/StateProcessor.java#L47).  This means that `ChainStorageClient.getBestSlot()` will not be updated during sync.  \n\nInstead of [pulling the best slot from `ChainStorageClient`](https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/blob/a99f47058d37d21f57567b632a9cffe9c03e3ddc/sync/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/artemis/sync/SyncManager.java#L138), we should keep track of the [latest slot that has been imported within `PeerSync`](https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/blob/a99f47058d37d21f57567b632a9cffe9c03e3ddc/sync/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/artemis/sync/PeerSync.java#L182) locally.  Suggest updating [`PeerSync.sync`](https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/blob/a99f47058d37d21f57567b632a9cffe9c03e3ddc/sync/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/artemis/sync/PeerSync.java#L61) to return an object that holds the sync future and sync status of the peer-sync being executed.\n\n",
